dcterms:creator: T. Camp
J. Boleng
V. Davies
dcterms:description: The random walk mobility model simulates the movement of mobile devices in a random manner, where each device moves to a randomly chosen location at each time step.
dcterms:title: Random Walk Mobility Model (RW)

dcterms:creator: T. Camp
J. Boleng
V. Davies
dcterms:description: The random waypoint mobility model allows mobile devices to move to a randomly chosen destination and pause for a specified duration before moving to the next destination.
dcterms:title: Random Waypoint Mobility Model (RWP)

dcterms:creator: X. Liu
Y. Liu
Y. Chen
dcterms:description: Cluster-based Q-learning (CQL) is a reinforcement learning approach used to optimize the deployment of multiple UAVs providing coverage to both static and mobile devices in a pre-partitioned area.
dcterms:title: Cluster-based Q-learning (CQL)

dcterms:creator: M. Mozaffari
W. Saad
M. Bennis
M. Debbah
dcterms:description: Iterative Search (IS) is an algorithm designed to optimize the placement and movement of UAVs for energy-efficient communication in IoT applications.
dcterms:title: Iterative Search (IS)

dcterms:creator: M. Mozaffari
W. Saad
M. Bennis
M. Debbah
dcterms:description: Exhaustive Search (ES) is a brute-force algorithm that explores all possible configurations for the placement and movement of UAVs to ensure optimal energy efficiency.
dcterms:title: Exhaustive Search (ES)
